TiddlyWiki Gotchas

Hard-won lessons about TiddlyWiki syntax and behavior. Read these BEFORE writing wikitext, filters, or creating tiddlers — they will save you from the most common mistakes.

Categories:

- **titles** — Tiddler titles with spaces, double-bracket syntax, list fields
- **filters** — Filter expression pitfalls (short-circuit, `:filter`, chaining, variables)
- **filter-runs** — How `~`, `+`, `:filter`, `:map` interact across runs (else, pipe, scope, interleaving)
- **wikitext** — Markup gotchas (`$reveal`, `code-body`, comments, `$let` vs `$set`)
- **shadows** — Shadow tiddler discovery (`[all[tiddlers+shadows]...]`)
- **slots** — `$slot`/`$fill` scope limitations, naming restrictions

